sentences: Amanda Meta Marshall (born August 29, 1972) is a Canadian pop-rock singer.
She is best known for her 1996 single, "Birmingham", which reached number 3 in Canada and was her only song to reach the US charts.
Marshall signed a recording contract with Metalblade Records in 1991, but both parties agreed that they were not a good fit and went their separate ways.
